Title: Danfoss AME 435 modulating actuator
Description: The Danfoss AME435 modulating actuator is designed for use with two and three-way valve types VRB, VRG, VF and VL up to a diameter of DN80 or with AHQM DN40 - 100. Automatically adapting its stroke to the valve end position, this self-stroking actuator reduces commissioning time for cost-effective, fast set-up. AME438's advanced design includes a load-related switch-off, keeping actuators and valves safe from overload while a spring-up safety feature retracks the actuating stem to end position in case of power failure or switch off without further manual stem positioning being disabled.

Title: SWL MZX 4601 1.1/2IN 3PORT LPHW VLV CV=20
Description: This globe construction Schneider Electric MZX seat valve with 1 1/2" female BSPP connection has a linear moving spindle and modified parabolic characterised plug, operating against the upper seat, which controls flow quantity to suit the load. The lower part of the plug has a linear characteristic, operating against the lower seat controlling bypass quantity, providing high  performance for mixing and diverting applications. For diverting use, the valve must be fitted in the return. Designed for operation by AVUM, AVUX and AVUE actuators, this valve is suitable for the control of hot or chilled water and brine or glycol solutions within specified limits.
